# Number of ordered quadruples \(w, x, y, z\) with gcd\(w, x, y, z\) \= 1 and 1 <\= \{w, x, y, z\} <\= 2^n\.
https://oeis.org/A343527


## Python
```Python
from labmath import mobius
def A343527(n): return sum(mobius(k)*(2**n//k)**4 for k in range(1, 2**n+1))
```
